[
    {
        "content": "<p>I've noticed that <code>x'</code> is a valid identifier in Lean4. Is it possible to locally override the tokenization rules so that <code>'</code> is treated as a postfix operator? If so, how would I do it?</p>\n<p>(I know I could just pick some other symbol for this example - I'm just trying to get my feet wet with modifying the syntax.)</p>",
        "id": 448922461,
        "sender_full_name": "Michal Wallace (tangentstorm)",
        "timestamp": 1720031524
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, the tokenization rules are basically hard-coded</p>",
        "id": 448952498,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1720041976
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can override them if you use a custom identifier parser, but this is a really heavy hammer and I wouldn't recommend it unless you are implementing a completely different language in lean</p>",
        "id": 448952602,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1720042042
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Fair enough, but do you know of an example?</p>",
        "id": 448954294,
        "sender_full_name": "Michal Wallace (tangentstorm)",
        "timestamp": 1720042761
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There is a TOML parser in lean core, which uses different identifier rules than lean</p>",
        "id": 448964766,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1720047378
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/master/src/lake/Lake/Toml/Grammar.lean\">Grammar.lean</a>?</p>\n<p>Isn't this just a parser written in lean? Or can this actually be used to embed TOML code in a .lean file?</p>",
        "id": 448967813,
        "sender_full_name": "Michal Wallace (tangentstorm)",
        "timestamp": 1720048955
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it's using the lean parser framework to some extent, but yes it's mostly just written from scratch</p>",
        "id": 448968831,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1720049565
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that is, you can take this as a \"no it's not possible\" if you like</p>",
        "id": 448968846,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1720049581
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hrm. Okay. I will stop thinking about this for now, then. :) Thanks.</p>",
        "id": 448969595,
        "sender_full_name": "Michal Wallace (tangentstorm)",
        "timestamp": 1720050046
    },
